pageContext.claim: “But some of the states are not doing well, let's face it. And some are doing phenomenally well. A state where Mike was governor, Indiana -- I looked at their numbers. They have -- it's incredible what they're doing.Some states are doing fantastically well. Iowa is doing great. You have -- you have states doing well, and you have some states that aren't doing well. We know the ones.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump creates the impression that a low case count means the state is having success. While that is part of it, that isn't the whole ball game. More than 10 percent of tests in states like Iowa are still positive, which indicates they have not yet reached the 5 percent positivity rate that WHO recommends before reopening.
